Argentine Stocks: Alto Palermo, Grupo Galicia, Macro, YPF Gain

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-05-18T20:23:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-18/argentine-stocks-grupo-financiero-galicia-and-ypf-advance.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The Merval Index rose 0.7 percent to 3,388.75.  Alto Palermo SA (APSA)   gained 9.9 percent to a record
18.90 pesos, the largest increase since November. The company
called a shareholder meeting for May 26 to vote on the
prepayment of as much as $37 million in bonds, according to a
statement posted today on the website of the Buenos Aires stock
exchange.  Grupo Financiero Galicia SA (GGAL)  , Argentina’s largest
consumer lender, climbed the most in a week, advancing 1.8
percent to 5.61 pesos. The price of Argentine sovereign bonds
rose today, which signals higher value for banks’ fixed-income
holdings.  Banco Macro SA (BMA)   increased 1.7 percent to 15.05
pesos.  YPF SA (YPFD)   advanced 1.9 percent to 193 pesos.
 Argentina ’s largest company by market value has gained 3.5
percent in the past two days after being rated “outperform” in
new coverage at Raymond James by equity analyst Diego Trucco.  To contact the reporter on this story:
